Charlie!

471
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:39,920
Ladies, come on in.

472
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:51,280
Thank you.

473
00:27:56,880 --> 00:28:00,960
<i>- Oh. That's too much.
- I'll pay, Baba.</i>

474
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:03,440
Don't be ridiculous.

475
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:06,160
Why not let her?
She makes more than you.

476
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:17,120
Aha!

477
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:19,440
You will make a beautiful bride.

478
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:23,160
<i>Thank you, Baba.</i>

479
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:29,000
<i>We'll take it. Oh, my beta.</i>

480
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:34,920
- Hello?
- Granger?

481
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:38,680
- Jennifer!
- Sounds like you're having fun.

482
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:40,080
Oh, it's a full-on rager.

483
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:43,160
<i>It's Charlie's big night,</i>

484
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:44,680
and the natives are a bit restless.

485
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:48,400
Next week, it turns out that I will
be able to meet you before the party,

486
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:52,360
so we can discuss the upgrade
we were talking about

487
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:55,680
when we were talking, before.

488
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:57,160
<i>That sounds great.</i>

489
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:59,080
I'd like that.

490
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:02,080
- It's the credit-card girl.
- Nice.

491
00:29:02,760 --> 00:29:04,400
I'll be in San Francisco on Thursday,

492
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:07,720
so maybe we can meet
at the Hawksin Grand Hotel?

493
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:09,600
<i>- You know where that is?
- Word.</i>

494
00:29:09,680 --> 00:29:11,440
Okay, let's say 6:00.

495
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:14,160
I'll be the dashing New Yorker
with unlimited credit.

496
00:29:14,200 --> 00:29:16,080
It's a date.

497
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:21,120
I mean, Thursday is the date of the day
when we'll meet.

498
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:22,480
<i>I'll see you then.</i>

499
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:34,080
You know you're crazy, right?

500
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:35,480
Hmm.

501
00:29:35,560 --> 00:29:38,680
What if this guy turns out to be
from a bad family and kidnaps you

502
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:42,680
and makes you clean their toilets and,
like, clean their dirty cats and all?

503
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:45,880
Then he's in real trouble.
I'm not a good cleaner.

504
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:48,200
<i>Bhaiya, Mumbai Airport.
Thank you, bhaiya.</i>

505
00:30:05,840 --> 00:30:07,280
<i>Thanks, bhaiya.</i>

506
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:15,440
You know you're playing with matches.

507
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:17,920
Fire? Why can't I have a little of that?

508
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:21,520
Why can't I have
just one amazing last adventure

509
00:30:21,560 --> 00:30:23,960
before I come back to Vikram?
This is my bachelor party.

510
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,680
I can't believe you're going all this way

511
00:30:25,760 --> 00:30:29,680
to see if this deranged guy is your Tom,
Richard, Harry, Hank soul mate guy.

512
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:32,520
- I don't know.
- I promise you, I'll be back in two pieces.

513
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:35,560
- You better.
- Wish the stars to shine bright on me.

514
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:42,800
<i>Mummy, Papa, please don't faint,</i>

515
00:30:42,880 --> 00:30:46,800
<i>but by the time you hear this,
I'll be on my way to America.</i>

516
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:50,400
<i>I know I should have told you,
but it was a last-minute decision.</i>

517
00:30:50,520 --> 00:30:55,600
<i>I left my heart</i>

518
00:30:58,680 --> 00:31:01,400
<i>In San Francisco</i>

519
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:11,000
<i>I've decided to attend
father's cousin sister's birthday party</i>

520
00:31:11,080 --> 00:31:15,440
<i>in Palo Alto.
It's been a long time since I've seen them.</i>

521
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:20,080
<i>I'll send everyone your regards.
And see you in five days, maybe.</i>

522
00:31:21,040 --> 00:31:22,240
Ouch!

523
00:31:23,160 --> 00:31:26,160
<i>And please don't panic,
I'm using my own savings.</i>

524
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:31,280
<i>Papa, remember how you always wanted
your little daughter to travel</i>

525
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:34,280
<i>and learn different cultures?</i>

526
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:35,720
<i>This is your gift to me.</i>

527
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:40,320
<i>The morning fog</i>

528
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:44,640
<i>May chill the air</i>

529
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:48,840
Hello. Welcome to Hawksin Hotel.

530
00:31:48,920 --> 00:31:50,560
- Have you got your passport on you?
- Yeah.

531
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:53,560
Great. Thank you.

532
00:31:53,640 --> 00:31:55,840
You're the behind-the-scenes
creative guy.

533
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:59,920
Yes, yes. No, and he knows why.

534
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:01,640
Mr. Hawksin.

535
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:03,880
Well, well.
Look who decided to get off their butts

536
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:05,040
and come fight for the job.

537
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:06,400
Never turn down a second chance.

538
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:09,440
The rooms are fantastic, by the way.
Thank you, sir.

539
00:32:09,520 --> 00:32:12,080
- May I speak, sir?
- Only to say thank you.

540
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,520
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

541
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:17,480
- We're gonna knock your socks off.
- And then he ruins it by speaking again.

542
00:32:17,560 --> 00:32:20,160
Didn't we talk about that?
Didn't I ask you not to speak so much?

543
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:22,680
Didn't I tell you to learn to listen?
Don't you want to be a nice boy?

544
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:27,280
Didn't I tell you to be more like him?
Here, watch this. Your hair is on fire.

545
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:32,800
But I don't want a Honda.
Learn from this.

546
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:39,000
Could you shut up? He doesn't like you.

547
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:41,440
He likes me.

548
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:51,600
I can't believe you're hooking up
with the credit-card girl.

549
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:56,680
No, wait, I believe it.
You're gutsy, pal.

550
00:32:57,000 --> 00:33:01,680
I mean, what if she turns out
to be this lonely housewife

551
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:05,720
with four kids and bad teeth and gout?

552
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:07,120
It's just drinks.

553
00:33:22,560 --> 00:33:23,960
Vibe?
- I got a good vibe.

554
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:25,080
Oh!

555
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:27,880
Just your type, 1 o'clock behind you.

556
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,520
- This one?
- Yeah.

557
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:33,240
Seriously.

558
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:37,680
That's her.

559
00:33:39,160 --> 00:33:41,720
- I'm going in.
- Good luck.

560
00:33:55,040 --> 00:33:57,600
- Excuse me, Granger Woodruff.
- Hi.

561
00:33:58,480 --> 00:34:02,600
- You're not Jennifer David?
- No. But I wish I was.

562
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:06,720
Sorry, I thought you were somebody else.

563
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:14,400
Excuse me, ladies...

564
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:18,720
You're not Jennifer David?

565
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:21,360
<i>- You didn't even talk to him?
- I couldn't, Zia.</i>

566
00:34:21,600 --> 00:34:24,960
I was frozen, stuck, like gum.

567
00:34:25,080 --> 00:34:26,560
Okay, so your crazy crush is over.

568
00:34:26,640 --> 00:34:29,480
<i>Just come home, we'll watch
Fatal Attraction and you'll be fine.</i>

569
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:30,680
Listen, this guy was no good.

570
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:33,480
I'm sure he lied about those charges
and he spends money like a maniac.

571
00:34:33,560 --> 00:34:34,760
He's not a liar.

572
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:37,880
And then he just, like, covers it all up.
It's just much better that you run now

573
00:34:37,960 --> 00:34:39,880
than be hot-glued to the floor later.

574
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:41,520
Maybe I expected too much.

575
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:44,040
<i>Besides, he didn't even
get a chance to meet me.</i>

576
00:34:44,120 --> 00:34:46,280
<i>If he did...</i>

577
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:49,040
You know, there was something
magical in our talk, Zia.

578
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:51,000
<i>- I promise you.
- Yes.</i>

579
00:34:51,080 --> 00:34:54,800
I do think that the American slang
for that is "bullshit."

580
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:57,400
<i>- Just come home, okay?
- Bye.</i>

581
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:05,800
So, your girl stood you up.

582
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:08,640
Come out to dinner with me and Karen's
best friend, it'll be good for a laugh.

583
00:35:08,720 --> 00:35:11,160
Discussing the intimate details
of bridesmaids' dresses

584
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:12,720
isn't my idea of a good time.

585
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:16,920
But you, my friend, you've got to take
this stuff seriously. It's your wedding.

586
00:35:18,560 --> 00:35:20,880
Let me know how the bouquets work out.

587
00:35:24,240 --> 00:35:27,080
Sorry. You okay?

588
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:32,680
- Gray...
- No, no, no, no. You... Do you see color?

589
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:37,680
Look, red bag. Red...

590
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:47,080
Keep the legs elevated.
I think you're gonna live.

591
00:35:47,840 --> 00:35:50,080
- I'm all right.
- I'm really sorry.

592
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:53,400
- I didn't see you.
- No, I... I wasn't looking, I was...

593
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:56,600
No, no, no. It's my fault. I feel awful.

594
00:35:58,160 --> 00:35:59,960
I wish you wouldn't...

595
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:04,680
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- No, I mean...

596
00:36:05,360 --> 00:36:07,600
I wish you wouldn't feel awful.

597
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:14,120
So, are you here on vacation?

598
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:22,320
Yeah, from India. I'm visiting a relative
at Palo Alto, just for a party.

599
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:25,920
Hey, I know this might sound odd,

600
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:28,800
and considering the dangers
of being with me and all,

601
00:36:28,880 --> 00:36:30,960
but you hungry?

602
00:36:31,640 --> 00:36:35,520
I was gonna go out to dinner,
and I thought you might want to come.

603
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:38,120
Oh! Um...

604
00:36:41,520 --> 00:36:46,640
That'll be nice, but only if it's ribs.

605
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:51,600
I read about this place in my guidebook.
You do like meat, don't you?

606
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:54,760
Yeah.

607
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:57,920
Mmm.

608
00:36:58,240 --> 00:37:01,160
They're delicious, thank you.

609
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:04,360
Granger Woodruff, by the way.

610
00:37:05,720 --> 00:37:07,760
Hello, Granger, I'm Priya Sethi.

611
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:11,240
Okay, Priya. You've got to just dig in.

612
00:37:11,640 --> 00:37:13,480
Okay? Don't...
Don't worry about getting messy.

613
00:37:13,560 --> 00:37:15,880
Just get it all over you.

614
00:37:15,960 --> 00:37:17,120
Okay.

615
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:21,040
So, what do you do in Mumbai?

616
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:26,080
- I'm a nurse. Yeah.
- Nurse.

617
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:28,160
It's quite nice.

618
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:31,400
- Good food.
- So...

619
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:34,760
- Is this your first trip to America?
- Yeah.

620
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:38,960
I always wanted to come,
and it's much more than I've expected.

621
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:42,680
- You're on vacation?
- I wish.

622
00:37:43,680 --> 00:37:47,880
I'm actually here for a business campaign.
I have this huge presentation next week.

623
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:51,960
Hey, maybe you can help me.
I mean, you're international clientele.

624
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:55,120
What attracted you to the Hawksin Hotel?

625
00:37:57,760 --> 00:38:01,280
- A friend told me about it.
- So you go on personal recommendations?

626
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:04,400
I mean, do you ever just
want to take a chance?

627
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:08,640
You know, like... Like the feeling
of trying something different?

628
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:12,840
I take chances, but usually
I can never afford them.

629
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:16,600
Charge it, you know, charge everything.
Just pay for it later.

630
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:20,080
Just don't let it get stolen.

631
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:22,720
Did someone steal your card?

632
00:38:22,840 --> 00:38:25,600
I have my ace credit-card girl
working on it.

633
00:38:25,680 --> 00:38:29,480
She was actually supposed to meet me,
but she blew me off.

634
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:33,520
Yeah. When someone opts out
of a prearranged appointment.

635
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:39,040
- For what purpose were you to meet her?
- Just casual.

636
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:40,880
She sounded nice.

637
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:44,400
But her friends probably warned her
about meeting a complete stranger,

638
00:38:44,480 --> 00:38:46,560
and she probably thought I was psychotic,

639
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:49,520
or maybe she just took
one look at me and ran.

640
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:55,040
Excuse me, I...
I need to go to the restroom.

641
00:38:57,280 --> 00:39:01,560
Zia, it's me. Could you please connect me
to Granger? It's 4593330555.

642
00:39:01,640 --> 00:39:04,720
Why do you want to talk to him?
I thought you blew him out.

643
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:09,480
I don't want him to think I was rude, and
actually, we're having dinner right now.

644
00:39:10,040 --> 00:39:13,880
<i>- What? You told him you're Jennifer?
- No. It... It doesn't matter.</i>

645
00:39:14,040 --> 00:39:16,240
<i>We're meeting as our real selves,
and it's better this way.</i>

646
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:18,560
<i>So, could you please
connect me to Granger?</i>

647
00:39:18,640 --> 00:39:20,280
Priya, this can lead to no good.

648
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:25,080
Or it could lead to the perfect romantic
moment under the Golden Gate Bridge.

649
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:28,040
Listen, honestly, you've lost your head.

650
00:39:31,040 --> 00:39:32,160
Hello?

651
00:39:32,240 --> 00:39:34,240
Hello, Granger. It's Jennifer David.

652
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:36,920
Hey! Is everything okay?

653
00:39:37,560 --> 00:39:40,280
I'm afraid when you didn't show up,
I signed up with the Visa girl.

654
00:39:40,360 --> 00:39:42,000
<i>She threw in a hat.</i>

655
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:45,560
I wanted to apologize
about not making our appointment.

656
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:48,440
It turns out I'm out of town, after all.

657
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:51,080
That's cool. Maybe next time, then.

658
00:39:51,520 --> 00:39:54,920
Very good. It...
It sounds like you're at a restaurant.

659
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:59,240
<i>- Teddy's Barbecue. You been?
- Yeah. I was there recently.</i>

660
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:03,400
Excellent ribs.
It's very romantic, isn't it?

661
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:10,640
Yeah. You know, since you stood me up,
I'm actually here with a nice girl.

662
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:13,240
Of course, I did smack her in the head,

663
00:40:13,320 --> 00:40:15,520
which I wouldn't have done
if you did show up.

664
00:40:15,600 --> 00:40:18,880
Well, have fun with your friend.
I'm sure she's quite lovely.

665
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:25,400
Inside and out. Not to be conceited for her.
Enjoy your evening.

666
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:28,720
- Good night.
- Good night.

667
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,800
Oh, wow, she's so good.

668
00:40:48,880 --> 00:40:53,320
- Hello?
- Hello, sister. How're things there?

669
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:56,040
<i>- Ji, ask.
- Okay.</i>

670
00:40:56,600 --> 00:40:57,840
What I wanted to know, sister...

671
00:40:57,880 --> 00:40:59,800
Anji, just switch it off,
I can't hear a word.

672
00:41:01,040 --> 00:41:03,240
Has finally Priya arrived there?

673
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:06,640
Priya? No. Priya isn't here.

674
00:41:06,920 --> 00:41:08,080
Priya is not there?

675
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:12,680
One minute. One minute. Supposing...
Supposing she wants to give a surprise?

676
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:15,240
- Hang up. Hang up.
- Wait a minute, sister. What?

677
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:17,160
- Hang up the phone.
- She might want to give a surprise.

678
00:41:17,240 --> 00:41:18,760
- Hang up. Hang up.
- I just can't hang up just like that.

679
00:41:18,840 --> 00:41:19,760
- Quiet!
- Hang up.

680
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,160
<i>Haan, sister. In case Priya...</i>

681
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:24,880
In case Priya calls up,

682
00:41:24,960 --> 00:41:27,080
just tell her that...
Just inform us, okay?

683
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:30,600
<i>Stop it, ji, stop it.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, hello, phone...</i>

684
00:41:30,680 --> 00:41:32,640
He sounded very confused.

685
00:41:41,720 --> 00:41:44,880
- Woodruff. Well...
- Mr. Hawksin.

686
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:49,200
I'd like you to meet my wife, Haejin.

687
00:41:49,480 --> 00:41:50,960
- Hello.
- Hi. Granger.

688
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:56,160
I'd like to introduce you to a very good
friend of mine, Priya Sethi.

689
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:57,480
She's from Mumbai.

690
00:41:57,560 --> 00:41:59,760
Mumbai.
That's the New York of India, right?

691
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:01,880
I hear there's quite an explosion
of jobs there.

692
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:05,120
I like to think of New York
as the Mumbai of America,

693
00:42:05,200 --> 00:42:07,080
both with talented human resources.

694
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:14,320
- That's so sweet.
- Very impressive.

695
00:42:14,680 --> 00:42:16,920
Well, we opened a hotel in Mumbai in '98,

696
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:19,360
the Hawksin Standard at Nariman Point.
Do you know it?

697
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:23,040
It's beautiful. The use of
steel and glass is breathtaking.

698
00:42:23,160 --> 00:42:26,520
Thank you. We think so, too.
You're lovely. Isn't she?

699
00:42:26,880 --> 00:42:29,280
- She's lovely.
- Yes, she is.

700
00:42:29,560 --> 00:42:32,640
Has he invited you to our little shindig?

701
00:42:32,720 --> 00:42:35,800
- I was just about to, actually.
- Good, good. Hold on a second.

702
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:38,600
Mary Pat, this young lady has come
a very long way to be with us.

703
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:41,400
Would you give her our nicest room,
with fruit basket, extra chocolates,

704
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:42,920
flowers every day? On my account.

705
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:45,440
Very good, Mr. Hawksin.
- That's very generous, sir.

706
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:46,840
Don't be silly.

707
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:51,600
So, we'll move you to 1740. It's a nicer
floor with its own concierge service,

708
00:42:51,680 --> 00:42:55,280
and I'll put you under Mr. Hawksin's name
as his guest.

709
00:42:55,320 --> 00:42:57,320
Thank you. That's very kind of you.

710
00:42:57,400 --> 00:43:00,600
Not at all. One of the pleasures
of owning places like this,

711
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:03,080
doing nice things for nice people.

712
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:07,840
If you'll excuse us,
we'll say our good nights.

713
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:09,120
Good night.

714
00:43:09,280 --> 00:43:11,160
- Good night.
- Good night.

715
00:43:16,520 --> 00:43:18,840
Wow! I... You...

716
00:43:19,200 --> 00:43:22,840
You know, he really...
I've never seen him act like that before.

717
00:43:22,920 --> 00:43:25,760
- Yeah?
- That was amazing.

718
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:27,600
No, no.
Let me just get one thing right.

719
00:43:27,640 --> 00:43:29,560
Aren't you supposed to be
Priya's best friend?

720
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:30,840
Yes, Mr. Sethi.

721
00:43:30,920 --> 00:43:33,000
- Isn't she supposed to tell you everything?
- Yes.

722
00:43:33,080 --> 00:43:34,440
