or anything of that nature.

732
00:43:57,080 --> 00:43:59,840
- Elope? Who is talking about elope?
- Oh, God.

733
00:43:59,920 --> 00:44:01,920
Oh, my God. I have to go.
I have to go and get her.

734
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:04,440
- I have...
- No, no, no, Mr. Sethi! No, no!

735
00:44:04,520 --> 00:44:06,640
Mr. Sethi, I promise you,
she's coming back.

736
00:44:32,120 --> 00:44:34,240
Morning, Priya.

737
00:44:34,680 --> 00:44:38,160
Hey! Isn't it amazing?

738
00:44:39,600 --> 00:44:42,920
- I love rain.
- Yeah, yeah. It's... It's great.

739
00:44:43,880 --> 00:44:46,440
Hey, you're still going to meet me at
the restaurant tonight at 7:00, right?

740
00:44:46,520 --> 00:44:51,240
Yeah.
Hey, is this a fancy party or something?

741
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:53,960
Well, you might want to wear
something nice.

742
00:44:54,040 --> 00:44:57,360
I mean, not nice-nice. But, you know.

743
00:44:57,880 --> 00:44:59,080
Yeah.

744
00:45:02,320 --> 00:45:06,560
Well, I have some work to do,
but I'll see you tonight.

745
00:45:07,320 --> 00:45:08,480
Great.

746
00:45:15,160 --> 00:45:17,520
<i>Welcome to San Francisco International.</i>

747
00:45:17,640 --> 00:45:19,120
Now, the moment we find our luggage,

748
00:45:19,200 --> 00:45:21,840
- we'll go and find this Hawksin hotel.
- Careful, careful.

749
00:45:23,800 --> 00:45:26,760
- Rajiv Uncle!
- Who's this man talking to me like this?

750
00:45:26,920 --> 00:45:29,640
- I'm Sajarit from Punjab.
- Okay, how...

751
00:45:29,720 --> 00:45:32,440
I know it has been a little while
since Navinda's wedding, but...

752
00:45:32,520 --> 00:45:35,040
Your family owns that store in Hoboken.

753
00:45:35,120 --> 00:45:36,240
- Oh, yeah.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

754
00:45:36,280 --> 00:45:38,520
<i>- And she's my wife, Neha.
- Hello, namaste.</i>

755
00:45:38,600 --> 00:45:40,680
And you are here
for Rani Auntie's birthday.

756
00:45:40,760 --> 00:45:42,680
Of course, of course,
and we are getting late

757
00:45:42,760 --> 00:45:44,680
and we have to find a cab
and get our luggage first.

758
00:45:44,760 --> 00:45:46,200
Come, come, come.
I'll give you a ride in my car.

759
00:45:46,280 --> 00:45:48,080
No, no, no! We don't want a ride!

760
00:45:48,160 --> 00:45:50,080
My parents will be furious
if I did not give a ride.

761
00:45:50,160 --> 00:45:52,880
- Please, come with me. My car is quite big.
- No, no, no... It's fine, thank you.

762
00:45:52,960 --> 00:45:54,400
My car is fast. Neha, please hold this.

763
00:45:54,480 --> 00:45:55,720
- Okay.
- Come, come. Come, come, come.

764
00:45:55,800 --> 00:45:57,800
- Yeah, yeah, yeah. Okay, I'll help you.
- It's fine! It's fine...

765
00:45:57,880 --> 00:46:00,400
It's so good to see you.
Come, please, excuse me.

766
00:46:00,480 --> 00:46:04,040
And this is a most pleasant
surprise for us. Please accept tea.

767
00:46:04,120 --> 00:46:06,320
We thought, since you were coming
all the way from here

768
00:46:06,360 --> 00:46:09,320
to Mumbai for Priya's wedding,

769
00:46:09,400 --> 00:46:13,840
we thought it was important that we also
show our respects, by coming to...

770
00:46:13,880 --> 00:46:18,240
<i>Han ji. You know, but we are only sorry
that Priya and Govinda couldn't come.</i>

771
00:46:18,360 --> 00:46:21,880
- Priya is visiting friends.
- Friends.

772
00:46:22,840 --> 00:46:26,960
And Govinda, you know, so
busy with exams and cricket and all that.

773
00:46:27,000 --> 00:46:28,920
<i>- His final exam's going on.
- Han ji. Han ji.</i>

774
00:46:48,120 --> 00:46:51,400
Hi, sorry to disturb you.
Delivery for Priya Sethi.

775
00:46:51,480 --> 00:46:54,320
- Really? Thank you.
- Here you go.

776
00:47:06,600 --> 00:47:08,880
Anji, where is your boom box?

777
00:47:09,880 --> 00:47:11,800
- She's asleep.
- Okay.

778
00:47:13,240 --> 00:47:18,160
All right, we will find this Hotel Hawkskin
as quickly as possible.

779
00:47:18,200 --> 00:47:20,880
- Yeah.
- There, we will divide,

780
00:47:21,280 --> 00:47:23,280
locate Priya and take her home.

781
00:47:23,800 --> 00:47:26,560
Pimmi, you will stay here.
If there's a problem, we'll call you.

782
00:47:26,640 --> 00:47:29,200
<i>- No, no, no, no. I'm coming with you.
- Let her come, ji.</i>

783
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:31,080
- Okay. Huh?
- Rajiv? Where is he?

784
00:47:31,160 --> 00:47:32,960
- Hello.
- Hello.

785
00:47:33,040 --> 00:47:35,760
Oh, there you are.
Rajiv, please come down.

786
00:47:35,840 --> 00:47:39,720
Anji wants to show her dance. She's been
practicing specially for Rani Auntie.

787
00:47:39,800 --> 00:47:43,400
<i>But, Auntie ji's sleeping.
I don't think it's nice to disturb her.</i>

788
00:47:43,480 --> 00:47:47,160
Let her sleep. She sleeps through
everything. You, come down. Come.

789
00:47:47,240 --> 00:47:49,440
- Now?
- Oh, yeah. Why not?

790
00:47:50,080 --> 00:47:51,760
- Right now?
- Oh, yeah. Right now.

791
00:47:51,840 --> 00:47:55,280
Come on, she's all set with her music
in her hand. Please, Rajiv.

792
00:47:56,880 --> 00:47:58,680
Come on, Anji. Play some music. Come on.

793
00:48:01,080 --> 00:48:02,640
Shake it, Anji!

794
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:06,200
Isn't she wonderful, Rajiv?

795
00:48:08,880 --> 00:48:10,400
Come on, do it!

796
00:48:12,320 --> 00:48:15,720
Oh, I forgot. The Sawants are coming over
for dinner tonight.

797
00:48:35,160 --> 00:48:38,600
<i>Some day</i>

798
00:48:39,240 --> 00:48:42,760
<i>When I'm awfully low</i>

799
00:48:43,520 --> 00:48:47,280
<i>When the world is cold</i>

800
00:48:47,960 --> 00:48:50,480
<i>I will feel a glow</i>

801
00:48:50,560 --> 00:48:55,600
<i>Just thinking of you</i>

802
00:48:56,440 --> 00:49:02,800
<i>And the way you look tonight</i>

803
00:49:10,840 --> 00:49:12,200
<i>Lovely</i>

804
00:49:12,280 --> 00:49:13,640
Who's that?

805
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:16,640
Just a friend.

806
00:49:17,320 --> 00:49:19,400
First impressions can be deceiving.

807
00:49:19,480 --> 00:49:21,680
- The thing about this guy...
- Here we go.

808
00:49:21,720 --> 00:49:24,960
...he's all casual charm
like nothing gets to him,

809
00:49:25,040 --> 00:49:27,280
but really, complete softie.

810
00:49:27,360 --> 00:49:28,840
- Yeah?
- In college,

811
00:49:28,920 --> 00:49:32,960
he couldn't eat or sleep until this
girl he liked finally talked to him.

812
00:49:33,040 --> 00:49:35,480
- I think he actually threw up afterwards.
- What?

813
00:49:35,560 --> 00:49:37,280
The man knows
how to make an impression.

814
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:39,240
Wait, let me give you a little advice.

815
00:49:39,320 --> 00:49:40,840
Don't listen to drunk Americans.

816
00:49:40,920 --> 00:49:42,800
No, but I do agree with Charlie.

817
00:49:42,840 --> 00:49:45,720
You know, there's something more
than what you really show.

818
00:49:45,800 --> 00:49:47,880
What about you? Any secrets?

819
00:49:47,960 --> 00:49:51,600
Are you an Indian movie star
hiding in America as a tourist?

820
00:49:52,480 --> 00:49:54,920
Well, glad you could make it.
Enjoying yourselves, I hope?

821
00:49:55,000 --> 00:49:56,720
- Definitely. Thank you, sir.
- Thank you.

822
00:49:57,560 --> 00:49:59,000
It's a wonderful party.

823
00:49:59,080 --> 00:50:01,360
Same feeling as the rest of your hotels,

824
00:50:01,400 --> 00:50:04,160
a magical oasis
that springs from nowhere.

825
00:50:04,240 --> 00:50:06,240
It's so familiar.

826
00:50:06,320 --> 00:50:07,640
We need you now.

827
00:50:07,720 --> 00:50:09,240
Maybe I should hire her
for my ad campaign.

828
00:50:10,640 --> 00:50:12,040
She's a smart girl.

829
00:50:13,520 --> 00:50:15,600
- He's kidding, right?
- Yeah, he's kidding.

830
00:50:17,160 --> 00:50:18,720
Have fun, buddy.

831
00:50:19,840 --> 00:50:20,800
It's okay.

832
00:50:22,600 --> 00:50:25,440
Look, but don't touch.
Look, but don't touch.

833
00:50:25,840 --> 00:50:27,720
Do you know, when I was little,

834
00:50:27,800 --> 00:50:31,440
I always wanted to find the golden ticket
in that chocolate,

835
00:50:31,480 --> 00:50:33,680
like Willy Wonka,

836
00:50:35,200 --> 00:50:37,720
so that I could go somewhere new.

837
00:50:38,880 --> 00:50:40,920
I always wanted to know
who was gonna drink that chocolate

838
00:50:41,000 --> 00:50:43,440
- after the fat kid fell in it.
- Yeah.

839
00:50:45,200 --> 00:50:47,560
Did you just try to push me in?

840
00:50:47,640 --> 00:50:49,640
That was a tap and you're too heavy.

841
00:50:49,720 --> 00:50:51,880
You see,
I knew there was another side to you.

842
00:50:51,960 --> 00:50:55,640
On the outside, you're the psychic,
sweet nurse from India,

843
00:50:56,760 --> 00:50:58,480
but you've got a streak.

844
00:51:01,840 --> 00:51:04,960
You're right.
There are things you should know.

845
00:51:09,400 --> 00:51:11,200
- Talk. Talk.
- Are you mad?

846
00:51:11,280 --> 00:51:13,040
- No.
- Talk.

847
00:51:13,080 --> 00:51:14,680
I'll throw you in.

848
00:51:16,440 --> 00:51:18,640
I forgot to watch out
for drunk Americans.

849
00:51:20,800 --> 00:51:21,840
Oh, there you are.

850
00:51:21,920 --> 00:51:23,680
Listen, I know, I know,
I'm sorry to interrupt.

851
00:51:23,760 --> 00:51:25,480
Business first, I need you for a second.

852
00:51:25,560 --> 00:51:27,200
One of us will be right back.

853
00:51:34,880 --> 00:51:36,840
- Gee.
- What's up, buddy?

854
00:51:37,720 --> 00:51:41,040
- I just put something together.
- Oh, yeah? What's that?

855
00:51:41,800 --> 00:51:43,760
Well, call me cynical,

856
00:51:44,560 --> 00:51:47,200
but did you bring your Indian friend
Prius here...

857
00:51:47,280 --> 00:51:49,040
- Priya.
- Whatever.

858
00:51:49,120 --> 00:51:52,880
To show Hawksin you're some
free-thinking, international guy?

859
00:51:52,920 --> 00:51:55,320
"Look at me, I'm dating an Indian girl."

860
00:51:55,400 --> 00:51:57,880
Yeah, you...
You figured me out, Chuck.

861
00:51:57,960 --> 00:51:59,760
Oh, yeah.

862
00:52:02,200 --> 00:52:03,720
All right, all right.

863
00:52:08,720 --> 00:52:10,720
Priya! Priya, wait!

864
00:52:14,440 --> 00:52:16,640
- Where are you going?
- I'm going back.

865
00:52:17,880 --> 00:52:19,440
I think I've served my purpose.

866
00:52:20,520 --> 00:52:23,760
- What are you talking about?
- I hope I was impressive enough for him.

867
00:52:24,760 --> 00:52:25,680
I heard you.

868
00:52:25,760 --> 00:52:29,040
You only took me to the party
to make your boss happy.

869
00:52:29,600 --> 00:52:31,520
Is that why you bought me this dress?

870
00:52:32,280 --> 00:52:35,000
- So I wouldn't embarrass you?
- What?

871
00:52:35,080 --> 00:52:36,680
No, no.

872
00:52:41,080 --> 00:52:43,720
Okay, look, the thought did cross my mind

873
00:52:43,800 --> 00:52:46,160
